from zipfile import ZipFile

# specifying the zip file name
file_name = "C:\\Users\\vrooky-montzo\\Downloads\\plant-seedlings-classification.zip"
  
# opening the zip file in READ mode
with ZipFile(file_name, 'r') as zip:
    # printing all the contents of the zip file
    zip.printdir()
  
    # extracting all the files
    print('Extracting all the files now...')
    zip.extractall()
    print('Done!')

# Hint: Create a DataFrame with 3 columns: Name of image, Species/class/type of image & actual image..

dataset ="C:\\Users\\vrooky-montzo\\Downloads\\train"
X = []
y = []
labels = []

# list all folders inside train directory
for i in os.listdir(dataset):
    print(i)
    if i!= 'desktop.ini':
      labels.append(i)        
      for j in os.listdir(os.path.join(dataset, i)):
        # read each image inside train directory one by one
        dummy = cv2.imread(os.path.join(dataset, i, j))
        
        dummy = cv2.resize(dummy, (128, 128)) 
        X.append(dummy)
        y.append(i)
print(type(X))

from pathlib import Path
import pandas as pd
import cv2

image_dir_path = "C:\\Users\\vrooky-montzo\\Downloads\\train"
paths = [path.parts[-3:] for path in
         Path(image_dir_path).rglob('*.png')]
df_all = pd.DataFrame(data=paths, columns=['path', 'Image_label', 'Image_Name'])
df_all.drop(columns = 'path',axis = 0,inplace = True)
df_all["Image"]=""

# visualizing the random images in the dataset along with their labels
       
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt # MATPLOTLIB FOR PLOTTING
import numpy as np
def get_nrand_img(n):
      rand = np.random.randint(0, len(X), n) # Generating 10 random numbers out of total number of flowers
      print(rand)
      plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))
      for i,j in enumerate(rand):
          plt.subplot(1, len(rand), i+1)
          plt.imshow(X[j]) 
          plt.title("{}".format(y[j]))
          plt.axis('off')
      plt.show()

get_nrand_img(5)

In [13]:
new_train = []
sets = []; getEx = True
for i in X:
    blurr = cv2.GaussianBlur(i,(5,5),0)
    hsv = cv2.cvtColor(blurr,cv2.COLOR_BGR2HSV)
    #GREEN PARAMETERS
    lower = (25,40,50)
    upper = (75,255,255)
    mask = cv2.inRange(hsv,lower,upper)
    struc = cv2.getStructuringElement(cv2.MORPH_ELLIPSE,(11,11))
    mask = cv2.morphologyEx(mask,cv2.MORPH_CLOSE,struc)
    boolean = mask>0
    new = np.zeros_like(i,np.uint8)
    new[boolean] = i[boolean]
    new_train.append(new)
    if getEx:
        plt.subplot(2,3,1);plt.imshow(i) # ORIGINAL
        plt.subplot(2,3,2);plt.imshow(blurr) # BLURRED
        plt.subplot(2,3,3);plt.imshow(hsv) # HSV CONVERTED
        plt.subplot(2,3,4);plt.imshow(mask) # MASKED
        plt.subplot(2,3,5);plt.imshow(boolean) # BOOLEAN MASKED
        plt.subplot(2,3,6);plt.imshow(new) # NEW PROCESSED IMAGE
        plt.show()
        getEx = False

np.random.seed(seed)
model = Sequential()
model.add(Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu', input_shape=(128, 128, 3)))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2), strides=(2, 2)))
model.add(Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu'))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2), strides=(2, 2)))
model.add(Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu'))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2), strides=(2, 2)))
model.add(Flatten())
model.add(Dense(128, activation='relu'))
model.add(Dropout(0.5))
model.add(Dense(12, activation='softmax'))

model.compile(tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(), loss='categorical_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])

D. Select a random image and print actual label and predicted label for the same.

In [25]:
import random
l = random.choice(range(len(X)))
img_rand = X[l]
img_rand = cv2.resize(img_rand,(128,128))
img_rand= np.reshape(img_rand,[1,128,128,3])
#the true label 
label_true = y[l]
print(l,"The actual label of the randomly chosen image is,",label_true)
#the label predicted by the model
predict_x=model.predict(img_rand) 
classes_x=np.argmax(predict_x,axis=1)
print("The predicted label of the randomly chosen image is,", y[classes_x[0]])

1540 The actual label of the randomly chosen image is, Common Chickweed
The predicted label of the randomly chosen image is, Black-grass

The model performs very poorly with the three convolution layers with a fully connected neural network. No matter whatever hypertuning was done the accuracy was not increasing at all. The maximum accuracy attained was a mere 8.7%, due to which most of the predictions made by the model was wrong. Due to the lower memory space(8gb) the entire dataset (4750 images in the train folder)was not converted to the dataframe. Taking only 3000 images for training itself might be one of the reasons for the decreased accuracy.
